Install R and RStudio on Ubuntu 12.04/14.04/16.04
To code faster and without any hassel we all need to install R and R Stdio on different variant of Ubuntu
like Ubuntu 16.04 (xenial), 14.04 (trusty), and 12.04 (precise)


# Ubuntu 16.04 (xenial)
# Install R + RStudio on Ubuntu 16.04

$ sudo apt-key adv –keyserver keyserver.ubuntu.com –recv-keys E084DAB9

# Ubuntu 12.04: precise
# Ubuntu 14.04: trusty
# Ubuntu 16.04: xenial
# Basic format of next line deb https://<my.favorite.cran.mirror>/bin/linux/ubuntu <enter your ubuntu version>/
$ sudo add-apt-repository 'deb https://ftp.ussg.iu.edu/CRAN/bin/linux/ubuntu xenial/'
$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get install r-base
$ sudo apt-get install r-base-dev

# Download and Install RStudio
sudo apt-get install gdebi-core


# Ubuntu 14.04 (trusty)
# Install R + RStudio on Ubuntu 14.04

sudo apt-key adv –keyserver keyserver.ubuntu.com –recv-keys E084DAB9

# Ubuntu 12.04: precise
# Ubuntu 14.04: trusty
# Ubuntu 16.04: xenial
# Basic format of next line deb https://<my.favorite.cran.mirror>/bin/linux/ubuntu <enter your ubuntu version>/
$ sudo add-apt-repository 'deb https://ftp.ussg.iu.edu/CRAN/bin/linux/ubuntu trusty/'
$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get install r-base
$ sudo apt-get install r-base-dev

# Download and Install RStudio
$ sudo apt-get install gdebi-core
$ wget https://download1.rstudio.org/rstudio-1.0.44-amd64.deb
$ sudo gdebi rstudio-1.0.44-amd64.deb
$ rm rstudio-1.0.44-amd64.deb

# Ubuntu 12.04 (precise)
# Install R + RStudio on Ubuntu 12.04

sudo apt-key adv –keyserver keyserver.ubuntu.com –recv-keys E084DAB9

# Ubuntu 12.04: precise
# Ubuntu 14.04: trusty
# Ubuntu 16.04: xenial
# Basic format of next line deb https://<my.favorite.cran.mirror>/bin/linux/ubuntu <enter your ubuntu version>/
$ sudo add-apt-repository 'deb https://ftp.ussg.iu.edu/CRAN/bin/linux/ubuntu precise/'
$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get install r-base
$ sudo apt-get install r-base-dev

# Download and Install RStudio
$ sudo apt-get install gdebi-core
$ wget https://download1.rstudio.org/rstudio-1.0.44-amd64.deb
$ sudo gdebi rstudio-1.0.44-amd64.deb
$ rm rstudio-1.0.44-amd64.deb
